                            <comment id="14524111" author="rohini" created="Fri, 1 May 2015 22:14:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Math.max compares same keys&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14524142" author="daijy" created="Fri, 1 May 2015 22:30:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s a mistake. Fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14524156" author="rohini" created="Fri, 1 May 2015 22:35:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;org.apache.hadoop.mapreduce.MRJobConfig.COUNTER_GROUPS_MAX_KEY and org.apache.tez.mapreduce.hadoop.MRJobConfig.COUNTER_GROUPS_MAX_KEY are both equal to mapreduce.job.counters.groups.max. Shouldn&apos;t it be TezConfiguration.TEZ_COUNTERS_MAX?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14524165" author="daijy" created="Fri, 1 May 2015 22:38:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sure, updated.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14524173" author="rohini" created="Fri, 1 May 2015 22:40:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14524191" author="daijy" created="Fri, 1 May 2015 22:43:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch committed to both branch 0.15 and trunk. Thanks Rohini for review!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15051878" author="daijy" created="Thu, 10 Dec 2015 23:56:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This won&apos;t work in Oozie since Limits is imposed already in Oozie job. Pig cannot change it. Actually the MR counter code is not needed. Open &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-4760&quot; title=&quot;TezDAGStats.convertToHadoopCounters is not used, but impose MR counter limit&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-4760&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-4760&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to fix that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
